WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:01.839
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:01.839 --> 00:00:02.959
Praise the Lord.

00:00:02.959 --> 00:00:04.880
Thank you for joining me today.

00:00:05.074 --> 00:00:09.870
I'm going to talk about something pretty hard, but many of you don't know about my daughter and her testimony and the story of what she's been through.

00:00:18.390 --> 00:00:21.940
I thought I'd talk about it because there are a lot of new faces.

00:00:22.460 --> 00:00:26.020
Many of you do know, but many of you do not.

00:00:26.280 --> 00:00:31.771
For the ones who don't know, I'm going to talk about it because people ask, "What's the noise in the background when you do your videos?

00:00:32.453 --> 00:00:32.907
" They email asking what that noise is.

00:00:33.566 --> 00:00:36.080
They think it's a devil or something.

00:00:36.080 --> 00:00:39.910
That's my daughter, and she has special needs.

00:00:40.420 --> 00:00:48.000
When she was 18 months old, she got the flu shot.

00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:58.686
It's very hard to talk about, but I talk about it because one day I believe it's going to be the greatest testimony the world has ever seen.

00:00:59.017 --> 00:01:02.187
That's what I just keep saying to myself.

00:01:03.813 --> 00:01:04.560
She got the flu shot and was developing normally.

00:01:08.880 --> 00:01:14.360
Her Apgar scores were completely normal when she was born.

00:01:14.360 --> 00:01:15.669
Everything was completely fine.

00:01:15.669 --> 00:01:18.900
She was talking and making full sentences, like any two-year-old would do.

00:01:18.900 --> 00:01:22.100
She was starting to really develop and everything was okay.

00:01:29.360 --> 00:01:40.205
When we went in, her doctor suggested the flu was really bad that year and said every parent should have this done.

00:01:44.651 --> 00:01:52.880
As young adults, we were fearful of that, so I told the lady to go ahead and give her the flu shot.

00:01:53.200 --> 00:02:02.759
We got her the flu shot at the same time we gave her her measles,, and rubella shot, her MMR.

00:02:02.759 --> 00:02:10.225
Within just a couple of days, she ran a very high fever.

00:02:11.925 --> 00:02:24.110
All of a sudden, it's like she went from being a happy little girl developing normally to a child completely in a bubble.

00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:30.589
She lost all speech and just made weird humming noises.

00:02:30.589 --> 00:02:38.564
She went into a complete zombie state.

00:02:38.564 --> 00:02:45.261
It was so bad that I called the doctor and said, "Something is really wrong with our child.

00:02:45.261 --> 00:02:50.480
" My wife called and we demanded they see her.

00:02:50.480 --> 00:02:54.251
They said, "Oh, she's just having a little reaction to the flu vaccination and running a fever.

00:02:54.251 --> 00:02:54.823
It's okay.

00:02:54.823 --> 00:02:55.680
This will pass.

00:02:55.680 --> 00:02:57.142
Don't worry about it.

00:02:57.142 --> 00:03:00.000
" I said, "No, there's something much more wrong.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:02.027
There's something really wrong.

00:03:03.040 --> 00:03:04.935
" Megan got worse and worse.

00:03:07.580 --> 00:03:10.188
Her bowels stopped working.

00:03:10.188 --> 00:03:12.864
She wouldn't go to the bathroom anymore.

00:03:12.864 --> 00:03:16.836
Her belly would swell up to the size of a beach ball.

00:03:16.836 --> 00:03:26.916
As a child, she would hold her bowels for three weeks at a time without going and would cross her legs because of the sensation of going.

00:03:29.392 --> 00:03:38.295
It was so bad that she would swell up huge, and she'd be so impacted they thought they would have to perform emergency surgery on her because of the X-rays.

00:03:38.463 --> 00:03:41.110
It was absolute hell on earth.

00:03:41.110 --> 00:03:52.200
She started having the worst tantrums and biting herself.

00:03:52.615 --> 00:03:59.576
She would wipe feces all down our hall all day long with what she would dig out of her hiney.

00:03:59.576 --> 00:04:01.874
It was nasty.

00:04:02.137 --> 00:04:06.980
She would wipe it on furniture, her bed, and our walls.

00:04:07.270 --> 00:04:12.599
Every day I'd come home from work and Diana would be home with her, just weeping because of how bad the day was.

00:04:15.645 --> 00:04:20.239
She would take everything in the bathroom and put it in the kitchen and everything in the kitchen into the bathroom.

00:04:23.451 --> 00:04:26.440
She put things from the bedroom into the living room.

00:04:27.440 --> 00:04:30.240
Every year when we put up our Christmas tree, she would take all the ornaments and lights down.

00:04:30.986 --> 00:04:36.240
We'd go to bed at night, and then she would put them in a drawer in the kitchen.

00:04:36.240 --> 00:04:39.285
This went on for years.

00:04:39.285 --> 00:04:47.120
The severity is such that I can't even tell you with words how bad it truly was.

00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:52.653
She would get two hours of sleep at night, keeping us up all night long.

00:04:52.653 --> 00:04:59.733
Diana and I were walking zombies because of how tired we were.

00:04:59.733 --> 00:05:05.759
I would go to work and pass out in the hall because of how tired I was.

00:05:05.759 --> 00:05:15.227
When I was working on a Saturday cleaning the church, I would go into the men's stall and just lay my head over because I was too tired to function, even while driving.

00:05:15.227 --> 00:05:16.720
It was so bad.

00:05:16.720 --> 00:05:22.133
We would drive her around at night in the car just trying to get her to sleep.

00:05:22.693 --> 00:05:24.231
We had a diesel car and the vibration and loudness would help her fall asleep as we were driving.

00:05:34.760 --> 00:05:40.902
But the moment we stopped the car and tried to take her to her bed, she'd wake up.

00:05:40.902 --> 00:05:42.719
There was nothing that kept her asleep.

00:05:43.439 --> 00:05:55.480
I would sit in the house and rock her for hours as she would try to fall asleep, listening to Christian music to the point where if I hear those songs now, it bothers me.

00:05:55.480 --> 00:06:06.749
I can't listen to that music anymore because of how traumatizing those moments were.

00:06:07.068 --> 00:06:15.244
I know many of you have children with special needs or autism, and my heart goes out to you.

00:06:15.244 --> 00:06:16.834
I pray for you all the time.

00:06:17.063 --> 00:06:18.526
People send me letters.

00:06:19.760 --> 00:06:20.960
I remember those days when we didn't think she would be where she's at right now.

00:06:22.684 --> 00:06:25.260
I prayed and believed, but the doctors all told us she would never progress beyond the mental capacity of a two-year-old.

00:06:41.531 --> 00:06:42.046
He said, "She'll never talk.

00:06:46.080 --> 00:06:48.659
She'll never be potty trained.

00:06:48.659 --> 00:06:51.653
She'll never have a normal functioning life.

00:06:51.653 --> 00:06:54.220
You're going to be this way forever.

00:06:54.220 --> 00:06:59.253
Why don't you sign her over to the state and make her an orphan so you can start over and have a normal life?

00:07:05.279 --> 00:07:08.090
" I told him I'll never do that.

00:07:09.090 --> 00:07:11.497
I will raise this little girl and she'll be healed.

00:07:11.497 --> 00:07:15.859
He said we were in denial, in La-La Land.

00:07:15.859 --> 00:07:23.129
He said, "I have over 3,000 documented diagnoses since I've started my practice, and I've never one time seen a child like this get any better or have a normal life.

00:07:35.070 --> 00:07:35.440
" He said, "I'm telling you all, you are in denial," and basically he was rebuking us, telling us that we needed a reality check.

00:07:47.119 --> 00:07:47.639
Diana said, "Sir, you may have never had a child come out of this as severe as this, but we are going to be the first ones.

00:08:01.199 --> 00:08:08.253
We're going to be the ones who come back and tell you that Jesus Christ is a healer and she's going to come out of this.

00:08:08.666 --> 00:08:13.169
" We're still believing that after 20 years.

00:08:16.053 --> 00:08:19.780
We're standing on it and believing for the full manifestation.

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:25.647
I want you to know that even someone who has the relationship that I have with the Lord goes through things.

00:08:35.767 --> 00:08:39.599
Not everything is always roses.

00:08:39.599 --> 00:08:45.771
I think it's interesting because we watch other people on Facebook comment about what their child's going through, but I would never make public many things that I went through when Megan was first diagnosed.

00:08:55.626 --> 00:08:57.573
We didn't even say the word autism.

00:08:57.573 --> 00:09:00.133
I wouldn't even let you say it in my presence because I'm not claiming it.

00:09:01.588 --> 00:09:06.308
I don't have that.

00:09:06.308 --> 00:09:10.587
I'm resisting what the devil has tried to put on us.

00:09:10.587 --> 00:09:16.622
I refuse to acknowledge it and say, "Listen, this is what we have.

00:09:16.622 --> 00:09:18.044
" No, I am resisting.

00:09:18.044 --> 00:09:21.428
I am resisting it.

00:09:21.428 --> 00:09:23.400
I am not claiming it.

00:09:23.400 --> 00:09:26.116
I am denying its right to be here.

00:09:26.116 --> 00:09:30.560
And by claiming it and saying, "I have this," is not what we have.

00:09:30.560 --> 00:09:33.636
I am the healed resisting autism.

00:09:33.636 --> 00:09:34.898
I am the healed.

00:09:34.898 --> 00:09:37.855
She is the healed resisting autism.

00:09:39.920 --> 00:09:45.260
Whenever she makes those noises and those hums and all the things that she does, we don't even notice it anymore.

00:09:45.260 --> 00:09:49.180
We're so used to it because of how many years it's been going on—for 20 years.

00:09:49.180 --> 00:09:51.120
You just don't even think about it.

00:09:51.120 --> 00:09:53.813
But whenever somebody's watching your video, they're thinking, "What is that?

00:09:54.276 --> 00:10:00.943
" So I try to explain to y'all a little bit what we're going through.

00:10:01.644 --> 00:10:06.705
The Lord told me, "Brandon, I've called you to the healing ministry.

00:10:06.705 --> 00:10:14.275
I've called you to go into all the world and lay hands on the sick and they'll recover.

00:10:14.275 --> 00:10:17.931
" I said, "How am I going to do that?

00:10:17.931 --> 00:10:26.079
Whenever I pray for my little girl and I haven't seen the full manifestation, I'll be a hypocrite.

00:10:26.653 --> 00:10:41.056
If I've got a child that's overcoming this and we don't see the full manifestation, how am I supposed to go and pray for the sick and then tell them that Jesus is a healer, that you're a healer, whenever I don't even see my daughter's full manifestation?

00:10:41.056 --> 00:10:51.108
" I argued with him and he said, "Brandon, your daughter does not validate my word.

00:10:51.108 --> 00:10:53.279
My word validates itself.

00:10:53.279 --> 00:10:55.473
It's a pillar by itself.

00:10:55.473 --> 00:11:00.764
I don't need Megan's full manifestation to prove my word is true.

00:11:00.764 --> 00:11:03.984
My word is true and it stands alone.

00:11:03.984 --> 00:11:11.600
Regardless of your circumstances, just be obedient and do what I've called you to do.

00:11:11.600 --> 00:11:19.470
" I wrestled with this over and over again until he kept coming to me and said, "I want you to start a YouTube channel and do these things.

00:11:23.893 --> 00:11:24.027
" I wrestled with it for two years, pulling videos and not putting them on YouTube.

00:11:29.856 --> 00:11:33.400
For two years I did this before anybody would ever really look at it.

00:11:33.960 --> 00:11:39.973
I put a video up for a couple days and took it down because I felt so inadequate, so tormented by it.

00:11:47.909 --> 00:11:51.889
And the Lord told me, "I want you to do what I've called you to do.

00:11:51.889 --> 00:11:56.622
" Well, we went to a Billy Burke meeting—I always talk about Billy Burke.

00:11:59.133 --> 00:12:05.289
It was my birthday, and I went for a birthday present for me.

00:12:05.493 --> 00:12:11.755
I wanted to go see Billy Burke, and I was excited about it.

00:12:11.755 --> 00:12:18.020
We got there and had to sit at the very back because Megan was acting so bad.

00:12:18.310 --> 00:12:30.079
Before this, we went to Andrew Wommack to get him to pray for her, and she was in the back of the service in this hotel room in Norman, Oklahoma.

00:12:30.659 --> 00:12:40.169
There was a huge light switchboard on the back of the auditorium, and Megan decided she was going to throw a fit and push those buttons.

00:12:42.862 --> 00:12:51.613
In the middle of Andrew Wommack preaching his sermon, all the lights went out in the whole auditorium and it went completely black.

00:12:55.346 --> 00:13:00.660
There were probably 3,000 people in there or more, and it was complete—you couldn't see your hand in front of your face inside this auditorium with the doors closed.

00:13:03.940 --> 00:13:06.370
Andrew was on the front stage and he goes, "Hello?

00:13:06.370 --> 00:13:09.200
" You know how he's so real country.

00:13:10.569 --> 00:13:15.440
I literally thought I could crawl underneath the table and bury myself.

00:13:15.440 --> 00:13:16.840
That's how embarrassed I was.

00:13:16.840 --> 00:13:18.040
I was freaking out.

00:13:18.040 --> 00:13:20.320
I grabbed a hold of her and I said, "I'm so sorry.

00:13:20.320 --> 00:13:20.520
I'm so sorry.

00:13:20.987 --> 00:13:24.343
" It was in the middle of the thing and he's preaching and everybody's looking.

00:13:24.343 --> 00:13:26.194
He turned around looking at us like, "What happened?

00:13:26.446 --> 00:13:36.290
" When the guys came over with flashlights looking to try to turn on the lights again—they were renting the building and didn't know how to turn the lights on, but they didn't lock them.

00:13:37.065 --> 00:13:38.220
Megan did that.

00:13:38.605 --> 00:13:40.204
We were looking for prayer.

00:13:40.204 --> 00:13:43.040
I think he prayed for us, but nothing really happened.

00:13:43.360 --> 00:13:47.611
Nothing against him; nothing happened.

00:13:48.948 --> 00:13:50.195
Just being real.

00:13:50.906 --> 00:13:59.760
After it was all over, I walked away feeling so defeated because I knew that I was expecting something to happen at Andrew Wommack's service.

00:14:01.360 --> 00:14:10.400
We took her to that, and that was one of the only services we took her to for a long time because then we had people telling us that she had a devil.

00:14:10.400 --> 00:14:11.439
I told you all about that.

00:14:11.439 --> 00:14:20.480
I took her down to a ministry in the Dallas area, and they charged us $500 to try to cast the devils out of her.

00:14:23.173 --> 00:14:26.067
I'm not going to get into that.

00:14:26.480 --> 00:14:28.885
Then we took her to a Billy Burke service.

00:14:29.170 --> 00:14:32.840
When we went to the Billy Burke service, we sat at the very back.

00:14:33.120 --> 00:14:34.800
We were at a massive church, a huge church.

00:14:35.623 --> 00:14:39.599
There were so many people you couldn't stir them with a stick.

00:14:40.119 --> 00:14:49.1000
I was so disappointed because I wanted her to be down at the front and get prayed for, but so did everybody else that has needs.

00:14:50.720 --> 00:14:55.208
The lines were long for prayer and Megan was losing it.

00:14:55.884 --> 00:15:00.169
She was having one of her biggest meltdowns and she was pushing against me, freaking out.

00:15:00.418 --> 00:15:05.520
I carried her up to the front holding her, and she was resisting me and pushing off of me.

00:15:06.930 --> 00:15:11.550
He says, "Everybody who needs a miracle, get down to the very front.

00:15:11.550 --> 00:15:12.460
I'm going to pray for you.

00:15:12.460 --> 00:15:13.067
I'm closing the service.

00:15:13.253 --> 00:15:25.291
" I was so disappointed because there were people all around me that had a lot more issues, it seemed, than what we had—broken legs and all these things going on with their bodies—and they were looking for healing, too.

00:15:25.291 --> 00:15:27.476
But there were just too many people to pray for.

00:15:27.831 --> 00:15:38.514
All of a sudden, my wife comes over and stands next to me with my other two, and Braden was filming it like he always does.

00:15:39.222 --> 00:15:40.639
He films everything.

00:15:42.080 --> 00:15:46.700
Billy Burke, by the spirit of God, looks over at us and he says, "You two come here.

00:15:47.030 --> 00:15:51.017
" He calls us over for us to pray for him.

00:15:51.017 --> 00:15:52.583
And you'll see the video right here.

00:15:52.583 --> 00:15:53.634
"Is this your daughter?

00:15:53.634 --> 00:15:54.160
" "Yes, sir.

00:15:54.160 --> 00:15:56.195
Bring her over here.

00:15:56.195 --> 00:15:58.810
She was making all the noise over there, right?

00:15:58.810 --> 00:16:00.205
What's going on with your daughter?

00:16:00.205 --> 00:16:02.033
" "She got a flu vaccination.

00:16:02.033 --> 00:16:17.590
It caused autism.

00:16:17.600 --> 00:16:19.466
" "How old is she now?

00:16:19.466 --> 00:16:20.213
" "She's 13.

00:16:38.560 --> 00:16:39.947
" So that's the video.

00:16:40.640 --> 00:16:52.630
That was the day that Megan started—the day that Billy Burke prayed for our little girl and she started having bowel functions for the first time.

00:16:52.940 --> 00:17:04.034
She came home and for the first time had a bowel movement by herself and was able to go on the stool and was completely potty trained within a couple weeks.

00:17:06.840 --> 00:17:07.060
It happened within 24 hours, but it was after he prayed for her.

00:17:09.274 --> 00:17:15.199
Within a couple weeks, God started to restore Megan.

00:17:15.199 --> 00:17:22.869
We were able to start going to church without her freaking out after that visitation from the Lord.

00:17:22.869 --> 00:17:33.733
We weren't able to go into public places—we were not able to go eat in public places or go to church or go to Walmart or go to any of these places because Megan would have such a meltdown.

00:17:33.733 --> 00:17:44.347
We would try to put her in the buggy and as she got older, I'd put her in a wheelchair, to the point where I just sat out in the car because it was so rough.

00:17:44.347 --> 00:17:51.833
We have videos—we took her to stores; we've done it now to prove that we've taken her into places because we want to document it.

00:17:52.226 --> 00:18:02.747
When the full manifestation comes, God alone, with all the documents, will get all the glory for what he's done for Megan.

00:18:03.173 --> 00:18:16.400
One day I was praying and our staff at our church was having a harvest party—that's what we want to call it because we don't celebrate Halloween—but they were having a get-together at the pastor's house.

00:18:16.880 --> 00:18:23.793
Everybody was going over there for barbecue and refreshments, things like that.

00:18:24.320 --> 00:18:32.320
We couldn't go because we didn't have childcare for Megan because nobody really could watch Megan because of how bad she was.

00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:34.240
Megan would not act right.

00:18:35.030 --> 00:18:37.200
It was awful.

00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:46.559
So we never really left her with anybody because we knew that they couldn't handle it and we didn't want to hear it: "Megan was this, Megan was that.

00:18:46.559 --> 00:18:47.697
" Oh, I don't care.

00:18:47.697 --> 00:18:48.551
I live it.

00:18:48.551 --> 00:18:50.653
You know, keep your comments to yourself.

00:18:50.653 --> 00:18:52.820
So family, even family, I couldn't deal with it.

00:18:52.820 --> 00:18:54.080
Don't want to deal with it.

00:18:54.080 --> 00:18:55.330
"Megan wet in our chair.

00:18:55.330 --> 00:18:58.720
Megan peed or had a pee accident in our chair or ruined it.

00:18:58.720 --> 00:19:00.160
" I don't want to hear it.

00:19:00.160 --> 00:19:02.434
You know, I live it.

00:19:02.434 --> 00:19:04.286
She's destroyed three cars.

00:19:04.286 --> 00:19:06.820
I mean, seriously, that's how bad it was.

00:19:06.820 --> 00:19:19.280
So when people don't relate and they can't handle something, they attack it or they accuse or say, "Hey, this is what you should be doing.

00:19:19.280 --> 00:19:25.280
" And when you're doing all you can do as a father with a special needs child, I don't need any correction.

00:19:25.280 --> 00:19:31.300
You know, I need sympathy and I need you to love on me whenever you are down and you're hurt and bad.

00:19:31.300 --> 00:19:32.040
You get that?

00:19:32.040 --> 00:19:38.780
And a lot of people always feel like they have their suggestion of what they think you should be doing because they have it all figured out.

00:19:38.780 --> 00:19:52.620
They look at your life through their little magnifying glass going, "I see that you have a flaw here," and they have no idea because they've never been through anything in their whole entire life, but they have a suggestion and a cure for you.

00:19:52.620 --> 00:19:54.107
Does that make sense?

00:19:54.107 --> 00:20:04.079
But everybody who's never been through anything knows how to fix your situation until you've lived it for less than a 24-hour period.

00:20:04.559 --> 00:20:12.711
And even the people who have—this is interesting—the people who have even more of an opinion just encounter you and they think they can fix all your issues.

00:20:12.711 --> 00:20:16.320
But if you lived it for a week, you'd want to hurt yourself physically.

00:20:16.320 --> 00:20:17.609
You know what I'm saying?

00:20:17.609 --> 00:20:18.640
It was so bad.

00:20:18.640 --> 00:20:23.100
I wanted to run my car off a cliff so many days because I could not function.

00:20:23.100 --> 00:20:24.420
And that's how bad it was.

00:20:24.640 --> 00:20:24.987
Sleep?

00:20:24.987 --> 00:20:27.413
I wanted to run off a bridge.

00:20:27.413 --> 00:20:28.220
I wanted to self-harm.

00:20:28.910 --> 00:20:30.093
That's how bad it was.

00:20:30.093 --> 00:20:34.080
I spiritually had to grab a hold of it.

00:20:34.080 --> 00:20:39.938
And the reason I'm still here is because I had that will inside of myself by the Holy Spirit to say, "You can do this.

00:20:39.938 --> 00:20:47.760
You be a father to that child and you be a husband to that wife and you don't abandon them by being a quitter.

00:20:47.760 --> 00:20:51.968
" But there were so many days that I went to an evangelist.

00:20:51.968 --> 00:21:01.111
I had such a deep root of depression on me and I was so suicidal that the evangelist who was at the front of the church saw it on me.

00:21:01.111 --> 00:21:03.840
He called me up to the front and said, "Sir, you need to come up here.

00:21:03.840 --> 00:21:07.100
There's a devil of suicide trying to come against you and I'm going to pray for you right now.

00:21:07.100 --> 00:21:09.468
Jesus is going to set you free.

00:21:09.468 --> 00:21:12.184
" I was so broken at that time.

00:21:12.184 --> 00:21:14.274
I literally thought I was lost.

00:21:14.274 --> 00:21:15.808
I didn't think I was going to make it out of it.

00:21:16.240 --> 00:21:19.360
And I remember sitting in the back of that church just looking for something.

00:21:19.360 --> 00:21:23.745
I left early that morning thinking, "I'm not going to go home today.

00:21:23.745 --> 00:21:31.707
" Diana was at home with Megan, and I just thought, "I need help.

00:21:31.707 --> 00:21:32.178
I need help.

00:21:33.120 --> 00:21:36.267
" And I drove to this little town, Crescent, Oklahoma.

00:21:36.267 --> 00:21:39.657
And this man named Ronald was there.

00:21:39.657 --> 00:21:42.480
Ronald was there and he was preaching.

00:21:42.480 --> 00:21:47.928
And we had our son at this time; he was just a little baby.

00:21:47.928 --> 00:21:55.932
And I was so down with depression and suicide that I thought there's nothing else I can do.

00:21:55.932 --> 00:21:58.213
I just got to quit.

00:21:58.213 --> 00:22:01.980
And I went to the back of this church just looking for hope.

00:22:01.980 --> 00:22:04.960
And he called me out and he said, "Come down to the front.

00:22:04.960 --> 00:22:06.688
" And he laid hands on me.

00:22:06.688 --> 00:22:10.816
And I'm telling you, that spirit came off of me and broke off of me.

00:22:10.816 --> 00:22:17.190
And the power of God set me free.

00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:25.200
It changed me forever.

00:22:25.200 --> 00:22:30.040
Yeah, the spirit tried to come back, but I resisted it more and more because I knew what it was like to be free.

00:22:48.864 --> 00:22:49.120
And there's so many times when you get to that place of desperation that you don't feel there's a way out of the hole that you're in and you think the only way out is death.

00:22:51.200 --> 00:22:59.270
But I'm trying to tell you today that Jesus has a plan for your life.

00:22:59.280 --> 00:23:20.968
And if I would have done what I was thinking I was going to do back then, I wouldn't be here with my son right now preaching the gospel to you.

00:23:20.968 --> 00:23:24.431
There's a place of desperation.

00:23:24.431 --> 00:23:35.020
There's a place of darkness that some people will never know until you've been there.

00:23:35.020 --> 00:23:51.457
A place of hurt, a place of discouragement that is so deep and so vast that you don't know how you're ever going to fill that bubble because you think there's no way out.

00:23:51.457 --> 00:23:53.286
And I'm so thankful for Ronald.

00:23:54.680 --> 00:24:00.950
He was a missionary from Romania and he came over there and he prayed for me.

00:24:00.950 --> 00:24:05.080
He gave me a prophetic word and told me there's people that have abandoned you.

00:24:05.080 --> 00:24:08.063
And he gave me this word and it was dead smack right on.

00:24:12.959 --> 00:24:19.629
After he prayed for us, then I went and I got Diana and I said, "Oh my God, baby, I have hope.

00:24:19.629 --> 00:24:19.954
I have hope.

00:24:20.634 --> 00:24:22.410
This man called me out.

00:24:22.410 --> 00:24:23.733
You know the circumstance.

00:24:23.733 --> 00:24:27.896
" She didn't know how bad I was because I try to be strong all the time for her.

00:24:27.896 --> 00:24:35.840
And I went over and I grabbed her and I got the kids and I took her to this revival that night.

00:24:36.860 --> 00:24:44.976
He was at a Pizza Hut eating after church, and I took her over there and I said, "Let me just try to sow a seed.

00:24:44.976 --> 00:24:50.471
" Because I knew the power of a seed.

00:24:50.471 --> 00:24:55.140
It was maybe like 20 bucks; I don't know because we didn't have nothing.

00:24:55.140 --> 00:25:00.826
But I told her, "Let's just sow that in faith, believing for breakthrough in our household.

00:25:00.826 --> 00:25:10.738
Let's believe for what seemed impossible that God's going to turn it around.

00:25:10.738 --> 00:25:24.430
" I go over this story and I cry every time and it's still painful.

00:25:24.440 --> 00:25:29.253
So Diana got prayed for, Megan got prayed for, we all went home.

00:25:29.253 --> 00:25:33.127
But I was so broken by it.

00:25:33.127 --> 00:25:41.109
So now I go back to the thing where I told you we were at the party, and this happened right after that.

00:25:41.109 --> 00:25:42.387
That's what I'm trying to tell y'all.

00:25:42.387 --> 00:25:44.320
This happened right after that.

00:25:44.320 --> 00:25:56.846
So, it was October the 29th and I was standing at the sink doing dishes and I had just come home from work and I said, "Lord, do you hear any of my prayers?

00:25:56.846 --> 00:25:59.274
Have you abandoned me, Lord?

00:25:59.274 --> 00:26:02.369
Do you care that I'm going through any of this?

00:26:02.369 --> 00:26:04.620
Do you see the pain?

00:26:04.620 --> 00:26:05.520
" Just fussing.

00:26:06.140 --> 00:26:08.720
"Do you see the pain that I'm going through?

00:26:11.017 --> 00:26:15.223
" Just scrubbing the dishes.

00:26:16.799 --> 00:26:22.067
Diana's in there dealing with Megan and all of a sudden Jesus comes in.

00:26:22.067 --> 00:26:33.875
And this is the first time I can tangibly tell you he was not a vision; he was tangible, tangible like this.

00:26:33.875 --> 00:26:37.205
He shows up in the kitchen.

00:26:37.205 --> 00:26:39.920
The presence of God felt so much.

00:26:39.920 --> 00:26:45.463
I turned around as I'm fussing and Jesus said, "I've heard all of your prayers.

00:26:45.463 --> 00:26:55.707
" And I turned around and I melted on the ground because I could not stand in front of his presence.

00:26:55.707 --> 00:27:02.880
And he looked at me and he bent over—I can remember his face like it was yesterday.

00:27:02.880 --> 00:27:09.005
He laid his hand upon my shoulder and he told me, "Brandon, I've heard all of your prayers.

00:27:09.005 --> 00:27:12.919
" He said, "What do you have need of, son?

00:27:12.919 --> 00:27:16.714
" I said, "Lord, don't you know?

00:27:16.714 --> 00:27:17.720
" I said, "Megan.

00:27:18.167 --> 00:27:24.587
" And he said, "According to your faith, Brandon, be it done unto you.

00:27:24.587 --> 00:27:30.000
" I said, "Lord, I want Megan to be completely healed.

00:27:30.000 --> 00:27:33.559
" And he said, "She will start to amend from this.

00:27:33.908 --> 00:27:39.413
" And he ministered to me some things that I won't talk about, but he loved on me.

00:27:41.560 --> 00:27:43.000
It was private stuff.

00:27:43.000 --> 00:27:47.421
And he laid his hand on my hand and he blessed me.

00:27:51.051 --> 00:27:57.639
Diana comes around the corner and she doesn't see him, but she feels the presence of the Lord in the house.

00:27:57.919 --> 00:28:04.515
It was so strong and so powerful that it made her stand, holding to the wall.

00:28:04.515 --> 00:28:08.020
I remember her coming in and she said, "Oh my god.

00:28:08.020 --> 00:28:09.634
" She goes, "Are you dying?

00:28:09.634 --> 00:28:16.273
" because she thought I was going home because I was on the ground, heaped over, just weeping.

00:28:16.273 --> 00:28:25.222
And I was sobbing because the presence of the Lord so filled my house with the glory of the Lord when Jesus showed up.

00:28:26.640 --> 00:28:26.942
He touched me.

00:28:27.849 --> 00:28:28.453
He looks over and he smiles at her.

00:28:29.058 --> 00:28:30.457
He didn't say nothing.

00:28:30.457 --> 00:28:34.860
And she doesn't see it, but she feels the presence of the Lord.

00:28:34.860 --> 00:28:38.097
I said, "Baby, Jesus is here.

00:28:38.097 --> 00:28:38.651
Jesus is here.

00:28:39.760 --> 00:28:41.093
" She says, "I can sense.

00:28:41.093 --> 00:28:43.247
I can feel, but I don't see it.

00:28:43.247 --> 00:28:44.336
I don't see him.

00:28:45.480 --> 00:28:49.450
" And she stood there and she started weeping at the presence of the Lord.

00:28:49.450 --> 00:28:52.453
And the Lord told us that Megan was going to get better at that time.

00:28:54.178 --> 00:29:01.925
To make a long story short, I know there's some of this I'm never going to tell publicly.

00:29:01.925 --> 00:29:05.662
He blessed me and he talked about the ministry.

00:29:05.662 --> 00:29:08.679
That's all you need to know.

00:29:08.679 --> 00:29:12.980
Then he said to me, "Brandon, my father's calling me.

00:29:12.980 --> 00:29:14.135
I must go.

00:29:14.135 --> 00:29:20.680
" He turned around and, just as he came, he disappeared right out of my kitchen.

00:29:20.680 --> 00:29:22.145
I wept.

00:29:22.145 --> 00:29:29.017
I look over at Megan expecting her to be better, and nothing.

00:29:30.011 --> 00:29:46.920
You know the Bible says as they went they were healed; it wasn't instantaneous that Jesus healed some people, it was as they went.

00:29:46.920 --> 00:29:50.314
That was Saturday.

00:29:50.314 --> 00:30:00.194
So Monday she went to school and her teacher called me in the middle of the afternoon.

00:30:01.520 --> 00:30:07.335
She said, "Brandon, what did you do to Megan?

00:30:07.335 --> 00:30:08.648
Something's happened.

00:30:08.648 --> 00:30:11.445
" And I said, "Hold on, Kimberly.

00:30:12.188 --> 00:30:13.012
What do you mean?

00:30:13.012 --> 00:30:13.919
What did I do to Megan?

00:30:13.919 --> 00:30:16.000
What do you mean what happened?

00:30:16.000 --> 00:30:22.434
" and she said, "Explain to me how she's saying words.

00:30:22.434 --> 00:30:26.295
" She said over 50 parroted words today.

00:30:26.295 --> 00:30:37.430
We're talking a child that had no vocabulary at all, was not able to function at all, able to keep eye contact for the first time, and was repeating.

00:30:40.920 --> 00:30:47.417
She made a list of all the words that Megan was saying on a piece of paper and we still have that today.

00:30:47.417 --> 00:30:52.567
We still have it today because it was a miracle.

00:30:52.567 --> 00:30:59.629
Megan still says things like parroting things all the time now even, and she says, "I love you.

00:30:59.629 --> 00:31:01.730
" She says, "Hi Daddy.

00:31:01.730 --> 00:31:02.971
" She says, "Hi Mommy.

00:31:02.971 --> 00:31:04.982
" Those are the things Megan does now.

00:31:04.982 --> 00:31:08.840
She's starting, and it's becoming more and more every day.

00:31:09.300 --> 00:31:10.410
"I want food.

00:31:10.410 --> 00:31:11.385
I want water.

00:31:11.710 --> 00:31:21.166
" Things like that, from nothing at all to now starting to say little phrases.

00:31:21.166 --> 00:31:24.613
Yeah, it's been a long time, but we've stood.

00:31:24.613 --> 00:31:28.399
And Megan, we were so wanting to help her.

00:31:28.399 --> 00:31:30.506
We do ABA and do all this stuff.

00:31:30.506 --> 00:31:32.920
We thought we put it all on our credit cards.

00:31:32.920 --> 00:31:38.000
We did everything we could to try to help our child to get out of that because there was no government assistance.

00:31:38.000 --> 00:31:39.714
There was nothing really for Megan.

00:31:39.714 --> 00:31:43.559
They would only allot so much a month.

00:31:43.559 --> 00:31:45.235
So we just kept charging.

00:31:45.235 --> 00:31:46.390
We kept doing things.

00:31:46.540 --> 00:31:50.205
We had to file bankruptcy because we were trying to find her help.

00:31:50.205 --> 00:31:56.693
There were all these different doctors saying all these different things saying, "Hey, if you do this, this is going to work.

00:31:56.693 --> 00:32:11.039
If you do chelation, whatever, they run the IV and they do all the things through your body to pull the heavy metals out from the shots, doing enemas, all kinds of things with chelation or whatever it's called.

00:32:11.039 --> 00:32:13.146
" Sorry, I butchered the word.

00:32:13.146 --> 00:32:16.279
We did all of it.

00:32:16.754 --> 00:32:17.229
DAN!

00:32:17.229 --> 00:32:19.130
doctors, you name it.

00:32:19.130 --> 00:32:20.800
We spent thousands.

00:32:20.800 --> 00:32:27.495
DNA testing, magnet testing, all kinds of things over the years.

00:32:27.495 --> 00:32:36.530
It's kind of like the woman with the issue of blood whenever she said she spent all she had but she grew worse.

00:32:36.530 --> 00:32:39.574
That's the way it felt like with us.

00:32:39.574 --> 00:32:43.644
All of these things didn't help but Jesus.

00:32:43.644 --> 00:32:56.340
We went to a Billy Burke meeting and you saw what happened and the power of God came on Megan and that's why we're hooked to going to Billy Burke.

00:32:56.340 --> 00:32:57.867
Because we went and spent...

00:32:57.867 --> 00:33:00.126
we went to all the big healing evangelists.

00:33:00.126 --> 00:33:05.839
I'm not here to throw any of them under the bus because it's not their faith that does anything.

00:33:05.839 --> 00:33:07.639
I was seeking the anointing.

00:33:07.639 --> 00:33:14.779
But in a place of desperation, it was so bad that I didn't think we were even going to be able to stay.

00:33:14.779 --> 00:33:16.779
God pointed us out.

00:33:16.779 --> 00:33:18.308
God through him: "Hey, you two.

00:33:18.993 --> 00:33:19.949
Come over here.

00:33:19.949 --> 00:33:20.760
" You watched it.

00:33:20.760 --> 00:33:21.840
It was just God.

00:33:21.840 --> 00:33:27.359
There were hundreds of people, if not a thousand people up at the front or more, and God did that.

00:33:27.359 --> 00:33:29.485
And that was the beginning of our journey.

00:33:29.485 --> 00:33:32.667
Then we went to Eufaula, and now Megan's getting better and better and better.

00:33:32.667 --> 00:33:35.874
And we went to the thing in Fort Lauderdale.

00:33:35.874 --> 00:33:38.880
So when you say, "Brandon, why are you so addicted to going to Billy Burke?

00:33:40.640 --> 00:33:42.840
" because it's the first sign of hope.

00:33:42.840 --> 00:33:51.120
It was the first sign of true hope other than what I had whenever she was with that visitation from Jesus.

00:33:51.120 --> 00:33:53.952
That was a ten-year window.

00:33:53.952 --> 00:33:56.155
Almost ten years, whatever it was.

00:33:56.155 --> 00:33:57.332
It was a long time.

00:33:57.568 --> 00:34:01.520
Plus ten years before we saw any other things starting to get better.

00:34:01.520 --> 00:34:04.639
Then we went to a Billy Burke meeting and then it was like, boom!

00:34:04.639 --> 00:34:05.750
And now it's starting to roll.

00:34:05.750 --> 00:34:10.187
But I'm saying it's like what he always says: "God doesn't dangle a carrot.

00:34:10.187 --> 00:34:12.629
" Brandon, God doesn't dangle a carrot.

00:34:12.629 --> 00:34:20.570
He doesn't heal you partway without getting the full manifestation to dangle a carrot and tell you, "Well, I'm going to do part of it and not do the whole thing.

00:34:20.570 --> 00:34:22.868
" I believe Megan is a work in progress.

00:34:22.868 --> 00:34:24.426
That's where that all came out of.

00:34:24.426 --> 00:34:25.803
"I'm a work in progress.

00:34:25.803 --> 00:34:27.573
" We talk about it all the time.

00:34:27.573 --> 00:34:29.520
God, we're a work in progress.

00:34:29.520 --> 00:34:35.440
Regardless if we miss it, if we fall, if we stumble, whatever, we're a work in progress with life.

00:34:35.440 --> 00:34:40.440
And I believe there's a lot of you that are watching this video today that can relate some way.

00:34:40.440 --> 00:34:42.393
Maybe not all the way.

00:34:42.393 --> 00:34:45.264
Maybe your circumstances are a lot worse.

00:34:45.264 --> 00:34:48.800
Maybe your circumstance is you've been given a death sentence.

00:34:50.596 --> 00:34:55.280
But I'm telling you, it's the faith that keeps on keeping on.

00:34:59.166 --> 00:35:10.571
Whenever it doesn't look like you're going to get out of it, whenever it looks the darkest, is whenever you get that bulldog inside of you saying, "I'm not giving up.

00:35:10.571 --> 00:35:14.959
" It's like when I went to that Ronald meeting; it was like, "I need help.

00:35:16.079 --> 00:35:19.920
" When you come to your end: "I need help.

00:35:19.920 --> 00:35:21.269
I can't do this anymore.

00:35:21.269 --> 00:35:26.439
" And I know there's a lot of you that are in that place right now that say, "I need help.

00:35:26.439 --> 00:35:27.940
I can't do this anymore.

00:35:27.940 --> 00:35:34.451
" I had an email or something, somebody saying, "My husband's dealing with this and he's ready to hurt himself because of the fact that he has tinnitus in his ears.

00:35:36.920 --> 00:35:41.120
" And that's where this came out of after I did this video for people like that.

00:35:49.000 --> 00:35:57.920
Because I'm telling you, whenever you go through something and it seems that it's never going to stop and you think, "I'm just going to do myself in.

00:35:57.920 --> 00:35:59.370
I can't do this anymore.

00:35:59.950 --> 00:36:05.076
" And there's people that have all these things that go through and you think the only way out is death.

00:36:05.076 --> 00:36:08.329
The only way out of this circumstance is to quit.

00:36:08.329 --> 00:36:12.514
I'm trying to tell you as a living testimony that there's more.

00:36:12.514 --> 00:36:15.387
And God has a plan for your life.

00:36:15.387 --> 00:36:20.880
It's not for you to hurt yourself or do something silly that's forever permanent.

00:36:20.880 --> 00:36:25.536
Don't do something permanent for a temporary problem.

00:36:29.737 --> 00:36:31.520
This too shall pass.

00:36:32.480 --> 00:36:34.700
Those dark days will pass.

00:36:34.700 --> 00:36:39.417
I believe that God is a rewarder of those that diligently seek Him.

00:36:39.417 --> 00:36:43.279
And whenever it seems the darkest, light's just around the corner.

00:36:43.279 --> 00:36:46.800
I believe that your circumstances are going to change today.

00:36:46.800 --> 00:36:51.554
I'm here to tell you that I'm still walking through some of the valley.

00:36:51.554 --> 00:36:54.479
I'm still walking through the times of hardship.

00:36:54.479 --> 00:37:00.747
I'm still walking through the things that don't look in the natural that I tell you I deal with with Megan.

00:37:00.747 --> 00:37:02.949
We had a really rough day with her on Sunday.

00:37:02.949 --> 00:37:04.804
I didn't even go to church.

00:37:06.140 --> 00:37:09.520
But is it all falling?

00:37:24.293 --> 00:37:27.696
The world's falling in.

00:37:27.696 --> 00:37:28.112
Oh, no.

00:37:28.112 --> 00:37:28.943
I thought you were getting better.

00:37:28.943 --> 00:37:30.259
No, devil, you ain't stealing my victory.

00:37:30.259 --> 00:37:30.860
Get off!

00:37:30.860 --> 00:37:31.760
We're going to church.

00:37:31.760 --> 00:37:33.947
We're going to be a family.

00:37:33.947 --> 00:37:35.817
We're going to do these things.

00:37:35.817 --> 00:37:36.594
Do you understand?

00:37:36.594 --> 00:37:44.960
Even whenever the circumstance tries to change and it throws up in your face to try to get you down, to try to suck your joy out, that's whenever you stand the most.

00:37:44.960 --> 00:37:48.697
Whenever the waves and the storm winds blow, that's when you stand the most.

00:37:54.930 --> 00:37:55.220
And I'm here to tell you, sometimes it gets darker before it gets light.

00:37:55.220 --> 00:38:01.340
Sometimes the valley of the shadow of death feels like it's going to devour you.

00:38:01.340 --> 00:38:03.520
But He said He would never leave you, and He said He would never forsake you.

00:38:03.520 --> 00:38:06.620
Lo, and to the end of the earth, He said He would be with you always.

00:38:06.620 --> 00:38:11.119
Though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil because Thy rod and Thy staff, they comfort me.

00:38:13.111 --> 00:38:13.395
And that's why I say, my God has a big staff.

00:38:13.395 --> 00:38:17.061
My God has a big rod, and He's going to bust you in the head, devil.

00:38:17.061 --> 00:38:22.648
I'm not going to allow you to get me down and ever do that again.

00:38:22.648 --> 00:38:25.414
It's what you think on.

00:38:25.414 --> 00:38:30.480
What you think on the most becomes bigger in your life.

00:38:30.480 --> 00:38:37.629
Sometimes whenever all you see in front of your face is the problem, it's hard to see anything else.

00:38:37.629 --> 00:38:38.674
I get it.

00:38:38.674 --> 00:38:47.170
Whenever it's so close to your nose—your nose is in it and it's like poo and somebody's rubbing that in your face—the devil's rubbing in your face that you're never going to get out of this.

00:38:47.170 --> 00:38:54.760
'You're going to be in this hole forever,' and you're going to go, 'I can't breathe anymore.

00:38:54.760 --> 00:38:57.760
' I get it.

00:38:57.760 --> 00:38:59.137
But God!

00:38:59.137 --> 00:39:04.933
And I'm just here to tell you a little glimpse of hope and to tell you a little bit about my past to encourage you that you can keep on keeping on too.

00:39:05.813 --> 00:39:10.827
You can keep on keeping on.

00:39:13.540 --> 00:39:17.280
Yeah, sometimes we walk through it and we're crying.

00:39:17.280 --> 00:39:18.813
Sometimes we're walking and crying.

00:39:18.813 --> 00:39:20.286
I'm telling you, there are days I've cried.

00:39:20.286 --> 00:39:21.371
I cried today.

00:39:21.371 --> 00:39:22.708
Look at me.

00:39:22.708 --> 00:39:23.599
It's painful.

00:39:23.599 --> 00:39:30.759
But you still get up and brush yourself off and you don't give up on Jesus because He's never given up on you.

00:39:32.819 --> 00:39:34.863
Jesus has never given up on you.

00:39:34.863 --> 00:39:38.049
And I don't give up on my circumstances.

00:39:38.049 --> 00:39:40.425
I don't give up.

00:39:41.155 --> 00:39:44.696
Whenever I feel like He said, 'I want you to go and do this,' and I say, 'I can't do this.

00:39:46.424 --> 00:39:51.866
I'll be a hypocrite,' He says, 'Do it.

00:39:51.866 --> 00:39:53.920
' 'Yes, Lord.

