Praise the Lord.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
Thank you for joining me today.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.550
Well, I'm going to talk about something that's pretty hard, but there's a lot of you that don't know about my daughter and her testimony and the story of what she's been through.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
I thought I would talk about it because there's a lot of new faces.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
Now, there's many of you that do know, but there's many of you that do not.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.450
So, for the ones that don't know, I'm going to talk about it because people go, "What's the noise in the background when you do your videos?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
" And people ask, they email, "What's that noise?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
" They think that there's a devil or something.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
That's my daughter and she has special needs.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
When she was 18 months old, she got the flu shot.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.200
It's something that is very hard to talk about, but I talk about it because one day I believe it's going to be the greatest testimony that this world has ever seen.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
That's what I just keep saying to myself.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
But, you know, she got the flu shot and she was developing normally.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Her Apgar scores were completely normal when she was born.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
Everything was completely fine.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
She was talking.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
She was making full sentences, like any 18-month or two-year-old would do.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Because she was starting to really develop, everything was okay.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.450
And when we went in, her doctor suggested the flu was really bad that year and every parent should do this and you should have this done.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.150
You know, kids can be hospitalized, and as young adults we were fearful of that, so I told the lady, "Yeah, go ahead, let's give her the flu shot.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.750
" Well, we got her the flu shot and it was at the same time we gave her her measles, mumps, and rubella shot, her MMR.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
Within just a couple of days, she ran a very high fever.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.300
And all of a sudden it's like she went from being a happy little girl that was developing normally to a child that was completely in a bubble and lost all talking, lost all—just made weird humming noises.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
She went into a complete zombie state.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
It was so bad.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
I called the doctor and I said, "Something is really wrong with our child.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
" My wife called and we said, "We demand you see her.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
" "Oh, she's just having a little bit of reaction to the flu vaccination, running a high fever.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
It's okay.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
This will pass.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
Don't worry about it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
" I said, "No, there's something much more wrong.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
There's something really wrong.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
" And Megan got worse and worse.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
Her bowels stopped working.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
She wouldn't go to the bathroom anymore.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
Her belly would swell up to the size of a beach ball.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.150
As a child, she would hold her bowels for three weeks at a time without going and would cross her legs because of the sensation of going, I guess.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
I don't know.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:15.400
And it was so bad that she would just swell up huge and she'd be so impacted they thought they would have to have emergency surgery on her because we'd have to go in and do x-rays, and it was absolute hell on earth.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
She started having the worst tantrums.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
She started biting herself.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
She would wipe feces all down our hall all day long with what she would dig out of her hiney.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
It was—I'm telling you, it's just nasty.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
But she would wipe it on furniture.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
She would wipe it on her bed.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
She would wipe it on our walls.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
And every day I'd come home from work and Diana would come home.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
Sometimes Diana would be at home with her and she would just be weeping because of how bad the day was.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
She would take everything in the bathroom and put it in the kitchen, and everything in the kitchen into the bathroom.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.550
She put all the things in the bedroom into the living room, and every year we put up our Christmas tree, she would take all the ornaments down and all the lights down.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
We'd go to bed at night and then she would put them in a drawer in the kitchen.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
This went on for years.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
The severity of this is—I can't even tell you with words how bad it truly was.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
She would get two hours of sleep at night, keeping us up all night long.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
Diana and I were walking zombies because of how tired we were.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.450
I would go to work and pass out in the hall because of how tired I was when I was working on a Saturday cleaning the church.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.050
I would go into the men's stall and just lay my head over because I was so tired I couldn't function, even driving.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
It was so bad.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
We would drive her around at night in the car just trying to get her to sleep.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
And because we had a big diesel car, a diesel engine, it had a lot of vibration and it was loud.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
So the vibration and the loudness, she would fall asleep as we were driving.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
But the moment we stopped the car and tried to take her into her bed, she'd wake up.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
There was nothing that kept her asleep.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.300
She and I would sit in the house and just rock her for hours, trying to get her to fall asleep listening to Christian music, to the point where if I hear those songs now, it bothers me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
I can't listen to that music anymore because of how traumatizing those moments were.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.100
I know there are a lot of you who have children with special needs or a child with autism, and my heart goes out to you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
I pray for you all the time.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.850
People send me letters; there was one little boy whose mom sent us stuff, and I remember those days when we didn't think she would be where she is right now.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
I prayed and I believed, but the doctors told us she would never come out of the mental capacity of a two-year-old.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
They said she would never talk, never be potty trained, and never have a normal functioning life.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
He said, 'You're going to be this way forever.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
Why don't you sign her over to the state and make her an orphan of the state so you can start over?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
You're young, you can have a normal life.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
' I told him I would never do that; I would raise this little girl and she would be healed.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
He said, 'You kids are in denial.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
You're in La La Land.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.850
' He said, 'I've had over 3,000 documented diagnoses since I started my practice, and I've never once seen a child like this get any better or have a normal life.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
' He was rebuking us, telling us we needed a reality check.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.450
Diana said, 'Sir, you may have never had a child come out of this as severe as this, but we are going to be the first ones.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
We're going to come back and tell you that Jesus Christ is a healer and she's going to come out of this.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
' We're still believing that after 20 years.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
We're standing on it and believing for the full manifestation.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.750
I want you to know that even someone who has the relationship I have with the Lord goes through things; not everything is always roses.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.550
We watch other people comment about what their child is going through on Facebook, but I would never make public a lot of the things I went through when Megan was first diagnosed.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
We didn't even say the word 'autism.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.100
' I wouldn't let you say it in my presence because I wasn't claiming it; I was resisting what the devil tried to put on us.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
I refuse to acknowledge it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
I am the healed resisting autism; I am the healed, and she is the healed resisting autism.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
When she makes those noises and hums, we don't even notice it anymore because it's been going on for 20 years.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
When someone watches a video, they might think, 'What is that?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
' so I try to explain a little bit what we're going through.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
The Lord told me, 'Brandon, I've called you to the healing ministry.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
Go into all the world and lay hands on the sick and they'll recover.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
' I asked, 'How am I going to do that when I haven't seen the full manifestation for my own daughter?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
I'll be a hypocrite.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
' I argued with Him, and He said, 'Brandon, your daughter does not validate My word.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
My word validates itself.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
