00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
' I wrestled with this until He told me to start a YouTube channel.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.050
I wrestled with it for two years, pulling videos and refusing to put them on YouTube before anyone would really look at them.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
I felt inadequate and tormented.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
Finally, we went to a Billy Burke meeting.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
It was my birthday, and I wanted to go as a gift to myself.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
We had to sit at the very back because Megan was acting so bad.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
Before this, we had gone to see Andrew Wommack in Norman, Oklahoma, to get him to pray for her.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
She was in the back of the auditorium, and there was a huge light switchboard.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Megan decided to throw a fit and pushed those buttons.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
In the middle of Andrew Wommack preaching his sermon, all the lights went out and it went completely black.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
There were probably 3,000 people in there.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
Andrew, on stage, goes, 'Hello?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
' in his country way.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
I thought I could crawl under the table and bury myself; that's how embarrassed I was.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
I grabbed her and said, 'I'm so sorry.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
' The staff ran over with flashlights to try to turn the lights on again.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.750
We were looking for prayer, and I think he prayed for us, but nothing really happened—not that I have anything against him, but nothing happened.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
After it was over, I walked away feeling defeated because I was expecting something to happen at Andrew Wommack's service.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Then we had people telling us she had a devil.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
I took her to a ministry in Dallas where they charged us $500 to try to cast the devils out of her.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
I won't get into that.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
Then we took her to a Billy Burke service.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
When we went to the Billy Burke service, we sat at the very back of a massive church.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
There were so many people you couldn't stir them with a stick.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.400
I was disappointed because I wanted her to be at the front to be prayed for, but so did everyone else who had needs.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.750
The lines for prayer were long and Megan was losing it; she was having one of her biggest meltdowns, pushing against me and freaking out.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
I carried her to the front while she was resisting and pushing off of me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
He said, 'Everybody who needs a miracle, get down to the front.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
I'm going to pray for you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
I'm closing the service.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.600
' I was disappointed because it seemed like the people all around me had many more issues than we had—broken legs and all these things going on with their bodies—and they were looking for healing, too.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
But there were just too many people to pray for.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
All of a sudden, my wife came over and stood next to me with my other two.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.100
Braden was filming it, as he always does, and Billy Burke, by the Spirit of God, looked over at us and said, 'You two, come here.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
' He called us over for him to pray for us.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
You can see the video right here.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
'Is this your daughter?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
' 'Yes, sir.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
' 'Bring her over here.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
She was making all the noise over there, right?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
What's going on with your daughter?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
' 'She had a flu vaccination that caused autism.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
' 'How old is she now?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
' 'She's 13.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
' That was the day Billy Burke prayed for our little girl and she started having bowel function for the first time.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.500
She came home and had a bowel movement by herself for the first time, was able to use the stool, and was completely potty trained within a couple of weeks.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
It happened within 24 hours, and God started to restore Megan.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
