00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.250
We would try to put her in the buggy, and as she got older, I'd put her in a wheelchair, to the point where I just sat in the car because it was so rough.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
We have videos to prove that we've taken her places now because we want to document it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
When the full manifestation comes, only God will get all the glory with all the documentation for what he's done for Megan.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.100
One day I was praying while our church staff was having a harvest party—that's what we call it because we don't celebrate Halloween—at the pastor's house.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
Everyone was going for barbecue and refreshments, but we couldn't go because we didn't have childcare.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Nobody could watch Megan because of how bad she was.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
Megan would not act right; it was awful.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
We never really left her with anyone because we knew they couldn't handle it, and we didn't want to hear about it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
I didn't care; I lived it, so I told people to keep their comments to themselves.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
Even with family, I didn't want to deal with hearing that Megan had an accident or ruined a chair.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
I lived it; she destroyed three cars.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
That's how bad it was.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
When people can't relate to or handle something, they attack it, accuse you, or tell you what you should be doing.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.450
When you're doing all you can as a father with a special-needs child, you don't need correction; you need sympathy and love when you're down and hurting.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.450
Many people feel they have suggestions because they think they have it all figured out, looking at your life through a magnifying glass to find a flaw.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
They have no idea because they've never been through anything, yet they have a cure for you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
It makes no sense until you've lived it for even a 24-hour period.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.150
People who just encounter you for a moment think they can fix all your issues, but if you lived it for a week, you'd want to hurt yourself physically.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.050
It was so bad; I wanted to run my car off a cliff or a bridge some days because I could not function.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
I was so close to self-harm.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
I spiritually had to grab hold of it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.250
The reason I'm still here is that I had the will inside me, by the Holy Spirit, to be a father to that child and a husband to my wife and not be a quitter.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.050
But there were many days I went to an evangelist with such deep depression and suicidal thoughts that he saw it on me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
He called me to the front and said, 'Sir, you need to come up here.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
There's a spirit of suicide coming against you, and I'm going to pray for you right now.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
Jesus is going to set you free.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
' I was so broken; I literally thought I was lost and wasn't going to make it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
I remember sitting in the back of that church looking for something.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
I left early that morning thinking I wasn't going home.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
Diana was at home with Megan and the baby.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
I just needed help.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
I drove to a little town, Crescent, Oklahoma, where a man named Ronald was preaching.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
I was so down with depression and suicide that I thought I had to quit.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
I went to the back of that church looking for hope.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
He called me out, laid hands on me, and I'm telling you, that spirit broke off of me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
The power of God set me free and changed me forever.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
That spirit tried to come back, but I resisted it because I knew what it was like to be free.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
When you reach that place of desperation, you think the only way out of the hole is death.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
But Jesus has a plan for your life.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.050
If I had done what I was thinking of back then, I wouldn't be here with my son preaching the gospel to you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
There's a place of darkness and discouragement so deep that you don't know how you'll ever get out.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
I'm so thankful for Ronald.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
He was a missionary from Romania who came and prayed for me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
He gave me a prophetic word and told me there are people that have abandoned you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
And he gave me this word and it was right on—dead smack right on.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
After he prayed for us, then I went and I got Diana and I said, "Oh my god, baby.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
I have hope.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
I have hope.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
This man called me out.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
You know the circumstance.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
" She didn't know how bad I was because I try to be strong all the time for her.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
And I went over and I grabbed her and I got the kids and I took her to this revival that night.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.500
He was at a Pizza Hut, at a pizza place eating after church, and I took her over there and I said, "Let me just try to sow a seed.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
" Because I knew the power of seed.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
It made me like 20 bucks.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
I don't know because we didn't have nothing.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
But I told her, I said, "Let's just sow that in faith, believing for breakthrough in our household.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
Let's believe for what seemed impossible, that God's going to turn it around.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
" I go over this story and I cry every time and it's still painful.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
So Diana got prayed for, Megan got prayed for, we all went home.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
But I was so broken by it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
So now I go back to where I told you we were at the party and this happened right after that.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
That's what I'm trying to tell y'all.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
This happened right after that.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
It was October 29th and I was standing at the sink doing dishes.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
I had just come home from work and I said, "Lord, do you hear any of my prayers?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
Have you abandoned me, Lord?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Do you care that I'm going through any of this?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
Do you see the pain?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
" Just fussing.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
"Do you see the pain that I'm going through?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
" Just all the things, just doing dishes at the sink, scrubbing the dishes.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.550
Diana's in there dealing with Megan and all of a sudden Jesus comes in and this is the first time I can tangibly tell you he was not a vision; he was tangible.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
He shows up into the kitchen—the presence of God felt so much.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
I turned around as I'm fussing and Jesus said, "I've heard all of your prayers.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
" And I turned around and I melted on the ground because I could not stand in front of his presence.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
He looked at me and he bent over and I can remember his face like it was yesterday.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
He laid his hand upon my shoulder and he told me, he said, "Brandon, I've heard all of your prayers.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
What do you have need of, son?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
" I said, "Lord, don't you know?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
" I said, "Megan.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
" And he said, "According to your faith, Brandon, be it done unto you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
" I said, "Lord, I want Megan to be completely healed.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
" And he said, "She will start to amend from this.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
" And he ministered to me some things that I won't talk about, but he ministered to me and he loved on me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
It was private stuff.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
And he laid his hand on my hand and he blessed me and he was loving on me.

