Diana comes around the corner and she doesn't see him, but she feels the presence of the Lord in the house.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
And it was so strong and so powerful that it made her stand—hold to the wall.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
I remember her coming in and she said, "Oh my god.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
Are you dying?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
" because she thought I was going home because I was on the ground in a heap, just weeping.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.400
And I was sobbing because the presence of the Lord so filled my house with the glory of the Lord when Jesus showed up.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
He touched me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
He looks over and he smiles at her.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
He didn't say nothing.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
And she doesn't see it, but she feels the presence of the Lord.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
I said, "Baby, Jesus is here.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
Jesus is here.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.750
" She says, "I can sense.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
I can feel, but I don't see him.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
" And she stood there and she started weeping at the presence of the Lord.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
And the Lord told us that Megan was going to get better.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.100
To make a long story short—I know there's some of this I'm never going to ever tell publicly—he blessed me and he talked about the ministry.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
That's all you need to know.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Then he said to me, "Brandon, my father's calling me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.050
I must go.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
" He turned around and just as he came, he disappeared right out of my kitchen.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
I wept.

